import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('date')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['date'], data_grouped['price'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the average price of stocks over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    max_price_stock = data.loc[data['price'].idxmax()]
    max_stock_symbol = max_price_stock['symbol']
    max_stock_price = max_price_stock['price']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].max().plot(kind='bar')
    ax.axhline(max_stock_price, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Price: {max_stock_price:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which stock had the highest price in the given period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    unique_symbols = data['symbol'].unique()
    for i in range(len(unique_symbols)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(unique_symbols)):
            x = data[data['symbol'] == unique_symbols[i]]['price']
            y = data[data['symbol'] == unique_symbols[j]]['price']
            plt.scatter(x, y, label=f'{unique_symbols[i]} vs {unique_symbols[j]}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Price of Stock 1')
    plt.ylabel('Price of Stock 2')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
